article.headline: Old Dominion 77, Morgan State 62
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- John Waller scored 20 points and Alex Loughton had 18 points and 15 rebounds as Old Dominion beat Morgan State 77-62 on Saturday night. The Monarchs (2-3) led just 34-33 with 19:18 left, but outscored the Golden Bears 26-6 over the next nine minutes to open a 62-39 lead. Isaiah Hunter had 10 of his 16 second-half points in the run, which ended with a 13-0 burst that expanded the lead to 23. The Golden Bears (1-4) scored the next nine points to get within 62-48 with 7:29 left, but Morgan State got no closer than 13 the rest of the way. Aaron Andrews led Morgan State with 14 points and Ronald Timus added 10. The Golden Bears also hurt their cause with 20 turnovers while Old Dominion had just 10. Hunter finished with 18 points and Troy Nance had 10 for the Monarchs.
